==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cyanate
<hw>Cy"a*nate</hw> <pr>(s?"?-n?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>cuanate</ets>. See <er>Cyanic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A salt of cyanic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ammonium cyanate</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
remarkable white crystalline substance, <chform>NH4.O.CN</chform>, which
passes, on standing, to the organic compound, urea,
<chform>CO.(NH2)2</chform>.</cd></cs> <-- *note* there was an *error* in
the urea formula "<chform>CO.(NH)2</chform>" in the original -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cyanaurate</ent>⟦br⟧
